n=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> Why make the same post on both threads?<br>
<br>
Your position doesn't make sense.<br>
<br>
Verant nerfed spell dmg to 2/3 to correct an imbalance.<br>
<br>
How does it follow that a measure, any measure is required to correct that very justified balance decision?<br>
<br>
Let me outline just how much spell dmg wizards would put out if the 2/3 measure didn't exist.  This assumes you have dmg focus obtainable from your friendly neighborhood mage.<br>
<br>
Lure of Ice             =1k unresistable<br>
Crit Lure of Ice       = 2k unresistable<br>
Half Resisted SS      = 970<br>
Full Damage SS       = 1940<br>
Crit Half resisted SS = 1940<br>
Crit Full Damage SS  = 3880<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
This is why spell dmg is nerfed to 2/3.  Don't expect any compensation for this... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukainite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kainite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 6:30:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A few flaws in your calculations....</span><hr size=1> Spell crits are fairly rare, so I dont think it's fair to factor them in, unless you are willing to factor in double backstabs from horendous damage weapons (Tantor's Tusk type or better). Lure's are NOT unresistable, incredibly hard to resist. I have HAD my Lure's totally resisted (yes it has not happened more than say 5% tops), but to say 100% resisted is a bit skewed. BUT, I do agree with the damage nerf for spell damage, the problem as we all have agreed on the most, is twinkage for the resists. Without the damage nerf (and the twinkage), spells just did too much damage and ended the fight before it ever began, surprise or no surprise. That was it's intended purpose, mostly for lower levels, when nukes would flat out kill you in 3 or less casts, regardless of class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showPrevMessage?topicID=65.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showNextMessage?topicID=65.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif 